# Copy to .env.local and adjust as needed.
#
# VITE_API_BASE is OPTIONAL now. By default the frontend talks to the API on the
# SAME origin it was served from:
#   * Single-port (prod-like): `npm run build`, then the backend serves dist/ on
#     :8000 — leave this empty.
#   * Dev (hot reload): `npm run dev` on :5173 proxies /api → :8000 (see
#     vite.config.js) — also leave this empty.
# Set it only to point at a cross-origin backend (no trailing slash), e.g.:
# VITE_API_BASE=http://localhost:8000
